19:18.089 --> 19:19.756
to keep the facts straight,
Herman.

19:19.839 --> 19:21.714
Do you intend
to take notes, Miss?

19:21.798 --> 19:23.631
DELLA:
That's generally what I do.

19:23.714 --> 19:25.422
Unless you object.

19:26.297 --> 19:28.464
And you're a detective,
Mr. Mason?

19:28.547 --> 19:31.089
It's a fancy word
for a busybody, but yes.

19:31.172 --> 19:35.172
We've been working together
since, uh... when was it?

19:35.255 --> 19:36.756
Just after the war.

19:36.839 --> 19:39.172
Gave him his first job back
from France,

19:39.255 --> 19:41.798
-isn't that right, Perry?
-HERMAN: You served overseas?

19:41.881 --> 19:43.214
With lots of other farm boys.

19:43.297 --> 19:45.005
Mr. Mason was in the army,

19:45.089 --> 19:48.172
survived
the Battle of the Argonne.

19:48.255 --> 19:50.839
How can we help you,
Mr. Baggerly?

19:50.923 --> 19:53.756
HERMAN: It's not me
that needs help, Mr. Mason.

19:53.839 --> 19:57.005
Matthew and Emily Dodson,

19:57.089 --> 19:59.547
an unspeakable act...

19:59.631 --> 20:02.005
was visited upon them,
they're quite overwhelmed.

20:02.089 --> 20:04.255
E.B.: Consider us
at their service.

20:05.631 --> 20:09.631
-Friends of yours?
-Members of my church.

20:09.714 --> 20:12.130
Working people
without many resources.

20:12.214 --> 20:15.589
E.B.: Well, God has put you
in their path.

20:16.297 --> 20:18.005
Is this a--

20:18.089 --> 20:19.714
HERMAN: Radiant Assembly of God.

20:19.798 --> 20:23.047
-Right. On the radio.
-Sister Alice.

20:23.130 --> 20:25.756
A woman
of wonder-working power.

20:25.839 --> 20:29.047
I won't hesitate to say
that she changed my life.

20:29.130 --> 20:33.339
Do the Dodsons know
you contacted me, Herman?

20:33.422 --> 20:36.673
They're anxiously
awaiting your guidance, Elias.

20:36.756 --> 20:38.005
What about the police?

20:39.631 --> 20:40.714
How's that?

20:40.798 --> 20:42.714
Well, they'll be
on this hammer and tongs.

20:42.798 --> 20:44.089
Why not leave it to them?

20:48.839 --> 20:50.422
I'll be frank, Mr. Mason.

20:52.464 --> 20:55.214
I don't trust the Los Angeles
Police Department

20:55.297 --> 20:56.798
to do the job that's needed.

20:59.673 --> 21:01.005
Neither would I.

21:04.964 --> 21:07.673
(OVERLAPPING CHATTER)

21:12.631 --> 21:14.130
STEVE HOLCOMB:
So you found this upstairs?

21:14.214 --> 21:15.881
MATTHEW:
I told you, my wife did.

21:15.964 --> 21:17.839
-I was at work.
-And she called you?

21:18.631 --> 21:20.547
Yeah. Hysterical.

21:20.631 --> 21:22.506
Why neither one of you
call the police?

21:23.172 --> 21:24.297
Read the note.

21:25.005 --> 21:27.589
You can read, can't you?

21:27.673 --> 21:31.422
So your wife finds the note,
calls you, what she do next?

21:31.506 --> 21:32.881
MATTHEW:
How should I know? Ask her.

21:32.964 --> 21:34.464
DETECTIVE ENNIS:
We'll get to her in a minute.

21:34.547 --> 21:36.381
HOLCOMB:
You own a grocery store,

21:36.464 --> 21:38.881
-much money in that?
-What?

21:39.005 --> 21:40.422
HOLCOMB:
Nice house for a grocer.

21:40.506 --> 21:42.297
It can't be cheap to maintain.

21:42.381 --> 21:43.589
MATTHEW:
What's that supposed to mean?

21:43.673 --> 21:45.255
HOLCOMB:
How long does it take to get

21:45.339 --> 21:47.047
-from the grocery store to here?
-MATTHEW:
What difference does it make?

21:47.130 --> 21:48.381
-Easy, Matthew--
-How am-- Are you suggesting

21:48.464 --> 21:51.631
I had something to do with it?
What the hell?

21:51.714 --> 21:53.339
ENNIS: Just covering
all angles, Mr. Dodson.

21:53.422 --> 21:54.631
MATTHEW:
Where was I? Who saw me?

21:54.714 --> 21:55.964
I didn't kidnap my son.

21:56.047 --> 21:58.464
-I didn't murder my own son.
-E.B.: No one is saying you did.

21:58.547 --> 22:00.547
MATTHEW: Well, he is!
And he's dancing around,

22:00.631 --> 22:02.130
but that's what
he fucking thinks.

22:02.214 --> 22:04.214
E.B.: Maybe this is a good time
for a little break.

22:04.297 --> 22:06.547
Sound okay to you,
Detective Holcomb?

22:09.547 --> 22:10.923
Yeah. Why not.

22:11.005 --> 22:13.381
-E.B.: Get some fresh air.
-MATTHEW: It's all right.

22:13.464 --> 22:14.798
You treated me like--
you can't--

22:14.881 --> 22:16.464
-you can't just walk...
-E.B.: Easy now, Matthew.

22:16.547 --> 22:18.756
Let's have a little drink
of cold water, shall we?

22:19.756 --> 22:21.339
MATTHEW:
Water. Right, great idea.

22:21.422 --> 22:22.464
That'll fix everything.

22:22.547 --> 22:24.589
E.B.:
It's all part of the process.

22:25.547 --> 22:27.381
(COMMOTION OUTSIDE)

22:33.255 --> 22:36.255
(FLOOR CREAKING)

22:42.422 --> 22:46.756
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

22:50.089 --> 22:51.589
(CAMERA CLICKS)

24:20.130 --> 24:22.714
EMILY: Are you the man
that works with Mr. Jonathan?

24:25.547 --> 24:28.673
Yes, ma'am. Perry.

24:32.881 --> 24:34.506
I'm Emily Dodson.

24:35.381 --> 24:36.547
Charlie's mother.

24:43.589 --> 24:45.589
Offer you a cigarette,
Mrs. Dodson?

24:47.881 --> 24:49.756
If you promise not to tell
my husband.

24:51.547 --> 24:52.756
Wouldn't dream of it.

25:11.214 --> 25:12.255
EMILY: Thank you.

25:16.547 --> 25:18.589
You were in the war,
weren't you?

25:20.923 --> 25:22.964
The way you hold your cigarette.

25:23.047 --> 25:24.631
Hiding the ember in your palm.

25:25.589 --> 25:27.130
I guess I'm still trained
not to give them

25:27.214 --> 25:28.381
something to shoot at.

25:30.005 --> 25:32.047
Was your husband over there?

25:34.005 --> 25:35.047
Brother.

25:36.172 --> 25:39.047
I haven't seen him
since we left Missouri.

25:39.130 --> 25:41.589
I really wish they'd let me
clean in here.

25:43.756 --> 25:45.297
All this fingerprint dust--

25:46.923 --> 25:50.839
Can't help feeling that it
reflects poorly on me somehow.

25:51.881 --> 25:54.339
Oh, I don't--
I don't think poorly of you.

25:56.798 --> 25:57.798
God does.

25:59.798 --> 26:01.172
That's why I'm being punished.

26:06.130 --> 26:08.714
Do you have children, Mr. Perry?

26:08.798 --> 26:11.839
It's-- It's Mason.
Perry is my first name.

26:13.047 --> 26:14.172
I have a son.

26:16.005 --> 26:17.422
What's his name?

26:20.631 --> 26:21.798
Theodore.

26:21.881 --> 26:22.964
Teddy.

26:24.964 --> 26:26.381
How old?

26:26.464 --> 26:28.130
MASON: Nine in February.

26:32.172 --> 26:33.547
EMILY: Charlie likes turtles.

26:36.172 --> 26:37.297
Liked.

26:41.381 --> 26:42.964
What's your boy fond of?

26:47.130 --> 26:48.172
Firetrucks.

26:53.339 --> 26:54.673
(GRIMACING) I bet...

26:56.255 --> 26:59.214
nine is a good age for a boy.

27:04.923 --> 27:07.839
(SOBBING)

27:11.547 --> 27:12.714
So...

27:15.381 --> 27:16.589
I'm sorry.

27:23.964 --> 27:26.464
(TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING)

27:26.547 --> 27:27.839
MASON: Yeah, fine,
he's a hothead,

27:27.923 --> 27:30.005
but he's a little too touchy
if you ask me.

27:30.756 --> 27:31.964
And her?

27:32.047 --> 27:34.756
She was just sitting
downstairs the whole time?

27:34.839 --> 27:37.464
E.B.: She told the detectives
she gave the boy a bath,

27:37.547 --> 27:40.464
put him to bed,
fell asleep by the fire

27:40.547 --> 27:41.964
listening to the radio.

27:42.047 --> 27:44.381
DELLA: Actually,
she puts Charlie to bed,

27:44.464 --> 27:46.422
goes downstairs
to clean up the kitchen,

27:46.506 --> 27:48.381
goes back upstairs
to check on him

27:48.464 --> 27:50.339
then goes downstairs
and falls asleep

27:50.422 --> 27:51.756
listening to the radio.

27:52.798 --> 27:54.756
She doesn't twitch an eyelid

27:54.839 --> 27:56.631
while someone creeps
into her house

27:56.714 --> 27:58.506
and nabs her kid?

27:58.589 --> 28:02.130
-You think she's a drinker?
-DELLA: No. She's a mother.

28:02.214 --> 28:05.005
Feeding, changing,
burping, screaming,

28:05.089 --> 28:06.422
you wouldn't last a minute.

28:06.506 --> 28:08.839
MASON: Is this something
you know about?

28:08.923 --> 28:10.923
DELLA:
Call it an educated guess.

28:15.589 --> 28:17.506
MASON: All right.
You're the kidnapper,

28:17.589 --> 28:19.673
you have to case that house
long enough to know

28:19.756 --> 28:21.506
Matthew's hours
at the grocery store,

28:21.589 --> 28:23.798
the time Emily
gives Charlie the bath,

28:23.881 --> 28:26.506
then puts him down,
then falls asleep herself,

28:26.589 --> 28:28.297
unless you have someone
on the inside.

28:28.381 --> 28:30.422
Oh, so you agree
with the police.

28:30.506 --> 28:33.047
You think the Dodsons
had something to do with it.

28:33.130 --> 28:35.964
-I'm not agreeing with anyone.
-I sure hope not.

28:36.047 --> 28:37.339
I've stood with those two.

28:37.964 --> 28:40.214
That's grief, not guilt.

28:40.297 --> 28:42.214
MASON: I'm just pointing out
that someone knew

28:42.297 --> 28:44.089
they were good
for a hundred grand.

28:44.172 --> 28:45.631
How do you figure that
from a guy

28:45.714 --> 28:48.839
who sells pickled cucumbers
and aftershave?

28:48.923 --> 28:50.464
It's queer from both sides.

28:50.547 --> 28:51.923
DELLA: And the baby.

28:52.964 --> 28:56.589
Someone stood over Charlie
and stitched those eyes.

29:00.005 --> 29:01.673
Yeah,
it's a dark tone,

29:01.756 --> 29:04.255
long, long, deep, dark tone.

29:07.589 --> 29:09.881
(SIGHS) Wipe it off, gentles.

29:09.964 --> 29:11.547
We do what we're asked to do.

29:11.631 --> 29:13.881
Well, that's easy for you
to say.

29:13.964 --> 29:16.089
Detectives aren't gonna like me
over their shoulder on this.

29:16.172 --> 29:17.631
And I got a license
that could get pulled.

29:17.714 --> 29:18.923
E.B.: So you don't want the job?

29:19.005 --> 29:21.422
-MASON: Did I say that?
-(E.B. LAUGHS)

29:21.506 --> 29:24.464
Bring me a signature
and a check.

29:27.964 --> 29:28.923
Cheer up.

29:29.005 --> 29:32.089
Someone might throw
a shoe at you.

29:32.172 --> 29:34.589
And you, get your hands
off my liquor and yourself

29:34.673 --> 29:36.673
down to the Angel's Flight
in the morning.

29:36.756 --> 29:38.547
Be my eyes, son.

29:39.089 --> 29:40.297
Time and a half.

29:40.381 --> 29:42.506
-It's New Year's Eve.
-Earn it.

29:48.673 --> 29:50.839
(LUPE PANTING)

29:52.381 --> 29:54.631
(SPEAKING SPANISH)

29:58.255 --> 30:02.422
-(MOANING)
-(BED SQUEAKING)

30:10.381 --> 30:13.589
(MOANING INTENSIFIES)

30:13.673 --> 30:15.172
-(LUPE YELPS)
-(OBJECT CLANGS)

30:20.381 --> 30:21.923
LUPE: Very good, papi.

30:23.339 --> 30:25.214
(COW MOOS)

30:26.673 --> 30:28.422
I think she's jealous of me.

30:29.047 --> 30:33.673
(PANTING)

30:33.756 --> 30:37.297
Did you bring
some more of that tequila?

30:37.381 --> 30:38.631
LUPE: It's called mescal.

30:38.714 --> 30:40.839
And if you want some,
you better get it yourself.

30:40.964 --> 30:42.589
I ain't your fucking help.

30:49.005 --> 30:50.255
(CHUCKLES)

30:51.422 --> 30:54.130
Either take them off
or put them back on, papi.

30:54.214 --> 30:55.297
Make up your mind.

30:55.381 --> 30:57.172
MASON:
What are you in a rush for?

30:57.255 --> 30:59.881
-LUPE: I need sleep.
-Sleep here.

30:59.964 --> 31:01.923
LUPE: I sleep
in my own bed.

31:05.089 --> 31:06.964
I'll give you 6,000
for this dump.

31:07.047 --> 31:10.464
(LAUGHS) Six thousand
and she won't even sleep here.

31:11.214 --> 31:12.631
It's a fair price.

31:12.714 --> 31:14.089
It's a  price.

31:14.172 --> 31:16.089
It's a great fucking price.

31:16.172 --> 31:17.756
You don't even have citrus.

31:17.839 --> 31:19.506
You know I'm working
this one.

31:19.589 --> 31:20.923
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

31:26.047 --> 31:27.381
It's a big case.

31:27.464 --> 31:29.506
You don't usually do the bigs.

31:30.422 --> 31:31.673
I'm doing this one.

31:33.964 --> 31:35.631
Six thousand five hundred.

31:35.714 --> 31:37.255
(LAUGHS)

31:37.798 --> 31:39.464
Enjoy your bed.

31:39.547 --> 31:40.673
LUPE: I will.

31:47.756 --> 31:52.214
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

31:52.297 --> 31:55.172
MAN: And right there,
in that very window,

31:56.130 --> 31:58.047
sat the boy's parents.

31:58.130 --> 32:01.547
Watching, hoping,
tragically unaware

32:01.631 --> 32:06.547
that their tiny innocent
was already ascending to heaven

32:06.631 --> 32:10.464
in the clutches of this demon.

32:10.547 --> 32:13.339
This instrument of death.

32:14.297 --> 32:16.547
Thank you, ma'am.
Happy New Year, sir.

32:16.631 --> 32:19.547
-(WHISTLE BLOWS)
-(NEWSBOY HOLLERS)

32:56.756 --> 33:00.881
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

33:42.714 --> 33:43.923
(GUN COCKS)

33:47.089 --> 33:48.756
HOLCOMB: Looking for something?

33:49.589 --> 33:51.339
Close the blinds, Steve.

33:51.422 --> 33:54.506
Maybe I couldn't see him so good
and shot him by accident.

33:54.589 --> 33:58.005
Look, fellas,
if I... interrupted

33:58.089 --> 34:01.339
some sort of tender moment,
I sincerely apologize.

34:01.422 --> 34:02.464
Guy's a laugh riot.

34:02.547 --> 34:04.673
Take it easy with that thing.

34:04.756 --> 34:06.714
What the hell
are you doing here, Mason?

34:06.798 --> 34:08.422
You gotta know something stinks
around Dodson

34:08.506 --> 34:09.673
or else you wouldn't be here.

34:09.756 --> 34:11.756
Get paid to look into things.
That's what I'm doing.

34:11.839 --> 34:13.881
Hell with this.
We got him on a B&E.

34:13.964 --> 34:15.255
Let's run him in,
torch his license.

34:15.339 --> 34:17.381
-Get the fuck off me!
-HOLCOMB: Settle down!

34:17.464 --> 34:19.297
Ease up, goddammit.

34:24.297 --> 34:25.673
You got something
says Dodson's clean,

34:25.756 --> 34:27.964
you'll be doing him a favor
by letting us know.

34:29.964 --> 34:33.839
MAN: ...tiny innocent
was already ascending to heaven.

34:36.089 --> 34:38.381
Right after the Dodsons
found little Charlie dead,

34:38.464 --> 34:40.130
a green Phaeton goes
tearing up Hill Street,

34:40.214 --> 34:41.422
clipped the trolley.

34:41.506 --> 34:43.714
HOLCOMB: You think
that's our kidnapper?

34:43.798 --> 34:45.506
Where did you get
this Phaeton shit?

34:45.589 --> 34:47.381
Traffic cop working
the bottom of the flight.

34:47.464 --> 34:48.964
He didn't think anything of it
at the time

34:49.047 --> 34:50.339
because most cops are stupid.

34:52.422 --> 34:53.673
Go check it out.

34:54.506 --> 34:57.673
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

35:03.089 --> 35:04.172
(DOOR CLOSES)

35:05.631 --> 35:07.714
Your ape almost broke my camera.

35:07.798 --> 35:09.798
My ape would've broke your jaw.

35:09.881 --> 35:11.130
-Here.
-What's that?

35:11.214 --> 35:12.714
-For the car thing.
-(SCOFFS)

35:12.798 --> 35:14.589
Save it
for a better sketch artist.

35:14.673 --> 35:16.631
Man in hat?
That sure narrows it down.

35:16.714 --> 35:19.881
What about the guy on the phone
or the one in the car?

35:19.964 --> 35:21.422
Halfway to Rio is my guess.

35:21.506 --> 35:23.130
Is that why
you like Dodson for it?

35:23.214 --> 35:24.506
Got to arrest somebody.

35:24.589 --> 35:27.589
So you tie him up in a bow and
put yourself up for promotion.

35:27.673 --> 35:29.547
-That's tidy.
-Listen to you,

35:29.631 --> 35:31.964
pissing on my five bucks
because some sap thinks

35:32.047 --> 35:34.130
you can play cop?

35:34.214 --> 35:36.673
I already got the entire city
standing on my neck.

35:36.756 --> 35:38.297
So you enjoy the view
while you're up here

35:38.381 --> 35:41.631
with the real police
because I'm gonna nail Dodson.

35:41.714 --> 35:43.673
And when I do,
you're back on the bottom,

35:43.756 --> 35:46.214
feeding off runaways
and cheaters.

35:46.881 --> 35:48.381
Lock up when you leave.

35:50.631 --> 35:51.881
(DOOR CLOSES)

35:53.881 --> 35:55.547
MAN: Tragically unaware

35:55.631 --> 35:58.839
their tiny innocent
was already ascending to heaven.

35:58.923 --> 36:01.214
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

36:22.172 --> 36:23.297
Mason here, any messages?

36:23.381 --> 36:24.923
DIANE:
Mr. Strickland called, read me

36:25.005 --> 36:27.381
three paragraphs of something
called  Lipstick Girl,

36:27.464 --> 36:28.839
I did not write them down.

36:28.923 --> 36:29.923
Anything else?

36:30.005 --> 36:31.255
DIANE: Just Walt LeBaron.

36:31.339 --> 36:32.964
Hammersmith Pictures requests
the honor of your presence

36:33.047 --> 36:34.214
at his New Year's party.

36:34.297 --> 36:36.547
Two tickets for you at the
door, business to discuss.

36:37.130 --> 36:38.172
All right. Thanks, Irma.

36:38.255 --> 36:39.756
DIANE: Diane, goddammit.

36:40.589 --> 36:41.923
Yeah. Yeah, I know.

36:45.589 --> 36:48.798
We got five minutes
and you owe me four bucks.

36:49.464 --> 36:50.673
You said two.

36:50.756 --> 36:52.339
Two for him, two for me.

36:52.422 --> 36:53.631
That's four.

37:06.547 --> 37:07.631
Happy New Year.

37:29.255 --> 37:30.422
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS)

37:39.589 --> 37:41.339
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

38:34.214 --> 38:36.631
♪ ("IT DON'T MEAN A THING"
BY ELLA FITZGERALD PLAYING) ♪

38:36.714 --> 38:38.464
MALE SINGER:
♪ It makes no difference ♪

38:38.547 --> 38:41.381
♪ If it's sweet
Or hot, hot, hot ♪

38:41.464 --> 38:45.422
♪ Just give that rhythm
Everything you've got... ♪

38:46.964 --> 38:48.798
What the fuck am I doing here?

38:48.881 --> 38:50.005
You're getting paid.

38:51.673 --> 38:53.214
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

38:56.047 --> 38:57.589
PETE:
Looks like Groucho Marx.

38:59.547 --> 39:03.089
Lovely ladies, kind gentlemen,
welcome.

39:03.172 --> 39:07.130
1931 was gangbusters
for Hammersmith Pictures.

39:07.214 --> 39:10.172
1932 is gonna be even better

39:10.255 --> 39:13.923
because the brightest stars
in the sky live right here,

39:14.005 --> 39:16.506
-Mr. Dusty Rogers...
-PETE: Oh, shit.

39:16.589 --> 39:17.839
...hero of the prairies.

39:17.923 --> 39:19.506
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

39:19.589 --> 39:21.005
PETE: Shorter than I thought.

39:21.089 --> 39:23.172
They must use really
small horses in the movies.

39:23.255 --> 39:25.714
HAMMER: Ladies, how do you
like the continental...

39:25.798 --> 39:28.464
Hey... What are you gonna do
with your 300?

39:28.547 --> 39:30.339
I'm gonna get
a new pair of shoes.

39:30.422 --> 39:32.255
Maybe somewhat--
Are you listening to me?

39:32.339 --> 39:33.339
Mm-hmm.

39:33.422 --> 39:35.673
I say something,
then you say something,

39:35.756 --> 39:37.756
that's how conversation works,
Perry.

39:37.839 --> 39:40.839
He's scaring the Jesus
out of me right now.

39:40.923 --> 39:43.339
Mr. Petre Lupu.

39:43.422 --> 39:45.798
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

39:48.255 --> 39:50.464
