into the spirit of the thing.

39:51.798 --> 39:53.506
I saw the kid, Pete.

39:54.964 --> 39:56.005
The thread.

39:57.339 --> 39:59.089
-You all right?
-Yeah.

39:59.172 --> 40:00.881
HAMMERSMITH: If you should be
happening to be living

40:00.964 --> 40:02.631
-next to Miss America.
-Yeah.

40:02.714 --> 40:04.214
(LAUGHTER)

40:04.297 --> 40:06.881
HAMMERSMITH: I call her
the sweetest piece of strudel
I've ever seen.

40:06.964 --> 40:07.923
I'll be back.

40:08.005 --> 40:12.047
But you're gonna
call her Red, Miss Velma Fuller.

40:12.130 --> 40:15.089
(CHEERS AND APPLAUSE)

40:16.130 --> 40:18.089
Oh, just a little, right there.

40:18.172 --> 40:21.172
Oh, I'm sorry, Clara,
I can't help myself.

40:21.255 --> 40:23.047
Anyway, listen.
Happy New Year...

40:23.130 --> 40:24.214
No champagne tonight?

40:24.297 --> 40:25.964
Just the cash, Walt.

40:27.631 --> 40:29.673
-Can we do it this year?
-(CHUCKLES)

40:29.756 --> 40:32.047
...go see a Hammersmith Picture.
Thank you all.

40:32.130 --> 40:33.798
Okay, Mason.

40:33.881 --> 40:35.756
Okay. Let's get you paid.

40:35.839 --> 40:39.964
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

40:56.506 --> 40:58.172
HAMMERSMITH:
You know what we have here?

40:59.130 --> 41:00.506
Plenty of nothing?

41:00.589 --> 41:02.130
HAMMERSMITH:
Ten thousand square foot of it.

41:02.214 --> 41:05.589
Why? Because I'm waiting
on a ten-million-dollar line

41:05.673 --> 41:07.214
of credit from the Irving Trust.

41:08.214 --> 41:09.881
I liked it better
when we were bandits

41:09.964 --> 41:12.506
on the land from the picture
patents company.

41:14.214 --> 41:15.547
Let's see what you got.

41:27.255 --> 41:30.547
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

41:35.089 --> 41:37.589
With people starving
on breadlines.

41:39.547 --> 41:40.839
The negatives?

41:41.714 --> 41:43.214
They're somewhere safe.

41:43.297 --> 41:45.714
Oh, okay.

42:04.214 --> 42:07.089
HAMMERSMITH: Nice lighter.
Here's the thing...

42:08.089 --> 42:09.631
we said 200.

42:09.714 --> 42:11.047
Six hundred is fair,

42:11.130 --> 42:13.339
because I can get that
from the teller, easy.

42:13.422 --> 42:15.673
Let me tell you how I see it.

42:15.756 --> 42:17.839
People are desperate out there,
Mason.

42:17.923 --> 42:21.547
They're starving,
scared, hopeless.

42:21.631 --> 42:24.839
And for one little nickel,
what do we give them?

42:24.923 --> 42:27.005
The two hours in the dark,

42:27.089 --> 42:28.756
singing, dancing,

42:28.839 --> 42:30.631
laughter, tears, romance...

42:32.964 --> 42:33.964
hope.

42:35.297 --> 42:38.005
And here you come
on New Year's Eve

42:38.089 --> 42:39.506
and what you wanna do

42:39.589 --> 42:43.506
is take these poor suffering
people's hope away

42:43.589 --> 42:46.839
-for 400 measly bucks?
-I can be flexible on the price.

42:46.923 --> 42:48.506
It's not about the price.

42:49.130 --> 42:50.673
It's the principle.

42:52.255 --> 42:53.297
So...

42:53.839 --> 42:57.506
200 like we agreed

42:58.214 --> 42:59.297
minus...

43:01.506 --> 43:05.339
199 for all the bullshit.

43:10.297 --> 43:12.506
You need to think
about your actions.

43:13.673 --> 43:16.214
You need to decide
what kind of person...

43:17.214 --> 43:18.506
you wanna be.

43:26.964 --> 43:28.464
And the negatives

43:28.547 --> 43:30.339
when you have a chance.

43:31.964 --> 43:34.881
(GROANS)

43:46.255 --> 43:48.339
(PANTING)

44:00.047 --> 44:01.881
Fuck!

44:01.964 --> 44:06.047
♪ (UPBEAT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:16.381 --> 44:21.130
You get it?
Did you get the 600?

44:21.214 --> 44:23.631
-There.
-The fuck is this, a dollar?

44:23.714 --> 44:25.839
-I think I overplayed it.
-Oh, no, Christ.

44:25.923 --> 44:27.631
-No, no, no.
-I'm sorry, Pete.

44:27.714 --> 44:29.297
I got a family to feed.

44:29.381 --> 44:33.381
(CHEERING)

44:35.089 --> 44:36.756
And fuck you!

44:38.923 --> 44:42.964
♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

44:55.047 --> 44:56.673
Relax, he'll be here.

44:56.756 --> 44:59.297
He got a hot date maybe?

44:59.381 --> 45:01.673
BLACK HAT: Uh-oh.
Touched a nerve.

45:01.756 --> 45:03.547
I'm starting to think
he doesn't like us.

45:03.631 --> 45:05.172
PINKY RING: Why are you
still wearing that hat?

45:05.255 --> 45:07.506
Your picture's
on every front page in town.

45:07.589 --> 45:08.673
It's a fedora.

45:08.756 --> 45:11.130
One and half million
in Los Angeles.

45:11.214 --> 45:12.506
It looks good on me.

45:12.589 --> 45:14.297
None of this
was part of the plan.

45:14.381 --> 45:17.047
So jump off a pier
and swim to Tahiti.

45:17.130 --> 45:18.172
I'll take your share.

45:18.255 --> 45:20.214
My share of what? A noose?

45:20.297 --> 45:22.422
BLACK HAT:
No one's getting strung out.

45:28.839 --> 45:30.381
I should've run.

45:30.464 --> 45:33.089
The second I saw Charlie
done like that.

45:33.172 --> 45:34.923
His eyes, Jesus.

45:35.464 --> 45:36.547
I should've run.

45:36.631 --> 45:38.297
We all should have.

45:38.381 --> 45:40.798
But we didn't, did we, killer?

45:41.923 --> 45:43.631
(DOOR OPENS)

45:45.130 --> 45:46.297
(DOOR CLOSES)

45:46.381 --> 45:49.422
Evening, gentlemen.
Sorry I'm late.

45:49.506 --> 45:52.673
Bunch of drunk Sambos blocking
up the road singing and dancing.

45:53.464 --> 45:54.631
Spooks were so fucking happy,

45:54.714 --> 45:57.005
I didn't have the heart
to crack any skulls.

45:57.089 --> 45:58.673
Let's get this over with.

45:58.756 --> 46:00.339
ENNIS: No Auld Lang Syne?

46:01.881 --> 46:02.881
Okay.

46:14.381 --> 46:15.756
What the fuck?

46:15.839 --> 46:17.964
(GUNSHOTS)

46:25.339 --> 46:27.381
(CHOKING)

46:28.005 --> 46:29.297
They made the car.

46:29.381 --> 46:31.005
(GUN CLICKS EMPTY)

46:33.839 --> 46:36.005
(CHOKING)

46:37.881 --> 46:40.839
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

46:51.798 --> 46:53.172
(DOOR CLOSES)

46:55.673 --> 46:57.756
Fuck! Fuck!

46:59.214 --> 47:01.547
♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

47:16.547 --> 47:18.589
(FIREWORK SQUEALING)

47:45.255 --> 47:46.923
(SCREAMS)

47:58.130 --> 48:00.089
LINDA: Mailman said
it's a stamp short,

48:00.172 --> 48:02.714
wants me to pay for it.
I said I'd love to pay for it

48:02.798 --> 48:04.964
except my bum of an ex
hasn't sent me money a month.

48:05.047 --> 48:07.089
Yeah, it's been tight, you know?

48:07.172 --> 48:08.798
I haven't-- I don't know

48:08.881 --> 48:11.214
why the fuck I am arguing
with you about this,

48:11.297 --> 48:12.589
just put him on the phone.

48:12.673 --> 48:14.005
LINDA: He's already in bed.

48:14.089 --> 48:15.130
Well, then, wake him up!

48:15.214 --> 48:16.547
I'm his-- I'm his father.

48:16.631 --> 48:18.923
I get to talk to my son
on New Year's Eve.

48:19.005 --> 48:20.881
LINDA:
That was already last year.

48:20.964 --> 48:21.964
It's New Year's Day.

48:22.047 --> 48:23.964
Put him on the fucking
phone, Linda.

48:25.714 --> 48:26.756
(SIGHS)

48:31.422 --> 48:34.089
How long have you
been standing there?

48:34.172 --> 48:37.381
Long enough to see
you make a jackass of yourself.

48:37.464 --> 48:39.631
She hung up on me.

48:39.714 --> 48:42.547
You never call the ex
on New Year's Eve, papi.

48:42.631 --> 48:43.881
Hello, operator?

48:43.964 --> 48:46.339
Could I get, um,
a long distance call?

48:46.422 --> 48:49.339
City of Salinas,
Axminster 7-7181.

48:49.422 --> 48:51.339
What the hell happened to you?

48:55.756 --> 48:58.297
All right. Well,
I was just on that line,

48:58.381 --> 49:00.673
it is-- it is the number
of a heartless woman,

49:00.756 --> 49:03.089
but there is nothing wrong
with her ears,

49:03.172 --> 49:06.005
so keep it ringing.

49:06.089 --> 49:09.422
You know, my second husband
tracked me down to Caracas,

49:09.506 --> 49:11.881
I had to pull
my little .22 on him.

49:11.964 --> 49:14.089
(CHUCKLES)
They only shot the pendejo  in--

49:14.172 --> 49:16.214
Just a little longer, please?

49:16.297 --> 49:18.964
Do you-- Do you have kids,
operator?

49:19.047 --> 49:20.547
You have a heart?

49:22.422 --> 49:23.464
No heart.

49:27.506 --> 49:28.547
LUPE: Listen...

49:30.631 --> 49:32.839
I'm flying straight to Oaxaca.

49:33.714 --> 49:35.798
Knocking back some mescal,

49:35.881 --> 49:40.297
chewing on chapulines by sunset
next to someone dumb

49:40.381 --> 49:42.673
and good-looking
next to me, so...

49:43.381 --> 49:44.881
I thought of you.

49:48.089 --> 49:50.547
Love, romance, excitement?

49:51.422 --> 49:53.005
Hmm.

49:53.089 --> 49:56.714
All of-- All of life's
big thrills.

49:58.839 --> 50:02.047
Maybe you can get
cleaned up first.

50:04.923 --> 50:08.172
Everybody's up to something.

50:08.255 --> 50:12.547
Everybody's got an angle,
hiding something.

50:15.422 --> 50:18.589
And everybody is guilty.

50:20.381 --> 50:22.381
(CHUCKLES)

50:43.673 --> 50:45.297
They don't make these things
so good.

51:00.631 --> 51:01.839
Poor papi.

51:08.172 --> 51:11.631
There is a black angel
out there.

51:12.255 --> 51:16.005
A big, big, black angel

51:16.673 --> 51:18.673
with long fingers.

51:26.297 --> 51:27.964
Oh, fuck.

51:55.964 --> 51:59.172
♪ (SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

53:53.881 --> 53:56.130
So you like turtles?

54:11.964 --> 54:16.005
